descriptions.public: The Public network allows inbound connections to VMs (Controllers and Tenant VMs) from external networks (e.g., Internet) as well as outbound connections from VMs to the external networks.
descriptions.storage: The Storage network is used to provide storage services such as replication traffic from Ceph. Management network is used for Ceph Public traffic.
descriptions.management: The Management network is primarily used for OpenStack Cloud Management. It is used to access OpenStack services (nova-api, OpenStack dashboard, etc).
descriptions.internal: The Internal network connects all OpenStack nodes in the environment. All components of an OpenStack environment communicate with each other using this network.
descriptions.floating: This network is used to assign Floating IPs to tenant VMs.
descriptions.private: The private network facilitates communication between each tenant's VMs. Private network address spaces are not a part of the public network address space; fixed IPs of virtual instances cannot be accessed directly from the rest of the public network.
descriptions.baremetal: Separate network where baremetal nodes managed by OpenStack Ironic reside. This IP range is assigned to service OpenStack nodes.
descriptions.fuelweb_admin: The Fuel Master node uses the Admin (PXE) network to provision and orchestrate the OpenStack environment providing DNS, DHCP, and gateway services to a node before that node is provisioned.

networking_parameters.l2_vlan_description: Neutron supports different types of network segmentation such as VLAN, GRE, VXLAN etc. This section is specific to VLAN segmentation related parameters such as VLAN ID ranges for tenant separation and the Base MAC address.

networking_parameters.dns_servers_description: This setting is used to specify the upstream name servers for the environment. These servers will be used to forward DNS queries for external DNS names to DNS servers outside the environment.
networking_parameters.baremetal_parameters_description: The Baremetal network is used by OpenStack Ironic. OpenStack Ironic will manage the physical nodes attached to this network. This is not the IPMI network for the hosts.  This network is registered as a provider network in Neutron and used for provisioning and accessing the baremetal hosts.

storage.title: Storage Backends
storage.ceph_block: Use Ceph as backend for Cinder volumes
storage.ceph_object: Use Ceph as backend for Swift objects
storage.ceph_ephemeral: Use Ceph as backend for Nova
storage.ceph_image: Use Ceph as backend for Glance images
storage.cinder_help: By default, Cinder block storage uses LVM volumes shared over iSCSI. Ceph backend requires two or more Ceph-OSD nodes and the KVM hypervisor.
storage.glance_help: By default, Glance image service uses Swift object storage. Ceph backend requires two or more Ceph-OSD nodes.

additional.install_ceilometer_description: Ceilometer provides metering and monitoring of an OpenStack cloud.
additional.ironic_network_mode_alert: Ironic requires Neutron with VLAN segmentation as a network option.
additional.ironic_storage_mode_alert: Ironic requires Swift object storage as a backend for the Glance image service.
